<subSubSection id="C37A652EFF8D0A76FF0CFA01FEDAF88F" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDF36A5FF8D0A76FF0CFA01FEDAF88F" blockId="7.[151,1437,1442,1816]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="B914EAB7FF8D0A76FF0CFA01FEDFFA2B" bold="true" box="[151,274,1442,1468]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">Remarks:</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="54DB8807FF8D0A76FED4FA01FE78FA2B" box="[335,437,1442,1468]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D26FF8D0A76FE47FA00FD93FA2B" box="[476,606,1443,1468]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Goniaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruana">
<emphasis id="B914EAB7FF8D0A76FE47FA00FD93FA2B" box="[476,606,1443,1468]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">G. peruana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, deposited in the Hamburg Museum, was destroyed during the Second World War. In addition, the original species descriptions and key couplet (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF14B54FF8D0A76FB93FA6AFB42FA74" author="Duda" box="[1032,1167,1481,1507]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" refString="Duda, O. (1930) Die neotropischen Chloropiden (Dipt.). Folia Zoologica et Hydrobiologica, 2, 46 - 128, v - xix." type="journal article" year="1930">
Duda 
<number id="3DA82482FF8D0A76FBC9FA6AFB42FA74" box="[1106,1167,1481,1507]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" value="1930.0">1930</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) were not sufficient to distinguish between 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D26FF8D0A76FE17FA53FDC2F99E" box="[396,527,1520,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Goniaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruana">
<emphasis id="B914EAB7FF8D0A76FE17FA53FDC2F99E" box="[396,527,1520,1545]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">G. peruana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D26FF8D0A76FDD1FA53FD2CF99E" box="[586,737,1520,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Goniaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscurata">
<emphasis id="B914EAB7FF8D0A76FDD1FA53FD2CF99E" box="[586,737,1520,1545]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">G. obscurata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Our concept of 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D26FF8D0A76FC37FA53FBFDF99E" box="[940,1072,1520,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Goniaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruana">
<emphasis id="B914EAB7FF8D0A76FC37FA53FBFDF99E" box="[940,1072,1520,1545]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">G. peruana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on unpublished notes on the 
<typeStatus id="54DB8807FF8D0A76FF76F9B5FEE2F9A7" box="[237,303,1558,1584]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">types</typeStatus>
made by C.W. Sabrosky in Hamburg in 
<number id="3DA82482FF8D0A76FCB5F9B5FCA2F9A7" box="[814,879,1558,1584]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" value="1937.0">1937</number>
, and by examination of specimens that were identified by Sabrosky subsequent to his study of the 
<typeStatus id="54DB8807FF8D0A76FC8FF99EFC9BF9C0" box="[788,854,1597,1623]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">types</typeStatus>
. There are no discernable differences between 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D26FF8D0A76FA18F99EFECDF9EA" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Goniaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruana">
<emphasis id="B914EAB7FF8D0A76FA18F99EFECDF9EA" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">G. peruana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the 
<emphasis id="B914EAB7FF8D0A76FEF5F9C7FD51F9EA" box="[366,668,1636,1661]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicName id="4C604D26FF8D0A76FEF5F9C7FDDDF9EA" box="[366,528,1636,1661]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Goniaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscurata">G. obscurata</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D26FF8D0A76FDB0F9C7FD51F9EA" box="[555,668,1636,1661]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Goniaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opaca">G. opaca</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
complex based on external characters. Because there are no illustrations or descriptions of the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D26FF8D0A76FC9AF928FC48F933" box="[769,901,1675,1700]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Goniaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruana">
<emphasis id="B914EAB7FF8D0A76FC9AF928FC48F933" box="[769,901,1675,1700]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">G. peruana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we cannot determine whether 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D26FF8D0A76FB67F928FA4DF933" box="[1276,1408,1675,1700]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Goniaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruana">
<emphasis id="B914EAB7FF8D0A76FB67F928FA4DF933" box="[1276,1408,1675,1700]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">G. peruana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closer to 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D26FF8D0A76FE93F912FE6EF95D" box="[264,419,1713,1738]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Goniaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscurata">
<emphasis id="B914EAB7FF8D0A76FE93F912FE6EF95D" box="[264,419,1713,1738]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">G. obscurata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or to 
<emphasis id="B914EAB7FF8D0A76FE76F912FDADF95D" box="[493,608,1713,1738]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicName id="4C604D26FF8D0A76FE76F912FD90F95D" box="[493,605,1713,1738]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Goniaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opaca">G. opaca</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
To avoid attaching a species description to an existing name whose identity is questionable and for which no 
<typeStatus id="54DB8807FF8D0A76FD11F97BFD73F965" box="[650,702,1752,1778]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">type</typeStatus>
specimen remains, we prefer to treat 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D26FF8D0A76FB18F97BFACAF966" box="[1155,1287,1752,1777]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Goniaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruana">
<emphasis id="B914EAB7FF8D0A76FB18F97BFACAF966" box="[1155,1287,1752,1777]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">G. peruana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a 
<emphasis id="B914EAB7FF8D0A76FADDF97BFEDAF88F" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">species inquirenda</emphasis>
</paragraph>
